From: Paul Srisoontorn <psrisoontorn@nvidia.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] mcu-runtime: boards: enable fmc_cs1 in bootmcu overlay

Enable the second SPI NOR flash chip (fmc_cs1) in the AST2700 bootmcu
board overlay configuration.

Upstream-Status: Pending

Signed-off-by: Paul Srisoontorn <psrisoontorn@nvidia.com>
---
 apps/mcu-runtime/boards/ast2700_evb_ast2700_a1_bootmcu.overlay | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/apps/mcu-runtime/boards/ast2700_evb_ast2700_a1_bootmcu.overlay b/apps/mcu-runtime/boards/ast2700_evb_ast2700_a1_bootmcu.overlay
index abcdef0..1234567 100644
--- a/apps/mcu-runtime/boards/ast2700_evb_ast2700_a1_bootmcu.overlay
+++ b/apps/mcu-runtime/boards/ast2700_evb_ast2700_a1_bootmcu.overlay
@@ -92,6 +92,12 @@
 	spi-max-frequency = <25000000>;
 };
 
+&fmc_cs1 {
+	status = "okay";
+	spi-max-buswidth = <1>;
+	spi-max-frequency = <25000000>;
+};
+
 &spi0 {
 	status = "okay";
 	timing-calibration-disabled;
-- 
2.25.1
